# 6. 輝く秘訣

Airi's Sister: Sis, wake up! Everyone's already done eating breakfast!
Elementary School Airi: Mhm... Just a little bit longer...
Airi's Sister: What?! But that show's about to start. I know we have it set to record, but...
Elementary School Airi: That show...?
Airi's Sister: Yeah, you said you were really looking forward to watching it! What was it called? Close-up Professional, right?
Elementary School Airi: Close-up...? *Gasp*
Narrator: <The professional we'll be covering this week is the ever-popular idol, Hiyori!>
Elementary School Airi: M-Made it just in time...!
Narrator: <From her private life to everything backstage, we'll be taking a close look at what it's really like to be a brilliant idol!>
Elementary School Airi: (I get to see what Hiyori's like when she's not working...!)
Elementary School Airi: (I can't wait...)
Narrator: <This day begins with a meeting for a show.>
Elementary School Airi: (Oh, there's Hiyori! Even her day-to-day clothes are cute...!)
Staff Member: <I see. It would be good to include that song. Anything else you'd like to suggest?>
Hiyori: <It's a big venue, so I want to help everyone in the back feel like they're right near the stage.>
Hiyori: <I could try going out to the stands more than usual, and throwing some signed balls... I wanna do stuff to make them feel seen.>
Elementary School Airi: (Wow...)
Elementary School Airi: (I didn't know this was how you planned for shows...)
Camera Operator: <Are you headed to practice now?>
Hiyori: <Yes! My show's coming up, so I've been requesting night practices lately.>
Elementary School Airi: (Wait, but she just got out of that meeting!)
Elementary School Airi: (When does she take breaks and stuff...?)
Instructor: <Alright, let's have you go through your new song from the top.>
Hiyori: <Okay!>
Elementary School Airi: Wow...
Elementary School Airi: (Her moves are so sharp! She really is an amazing dancer...!)
Elementary School Airi: (I wanna learn how to...)
Instructor: <Stop!>
Elementary School Airi: Huh...?
Instructor: <You need to exaggerate each movement more, and express what you're feeling more clearly. No one is going to pay attention if you don't dance with more energy.>
Instructor: <Again, from the top.>
Elementary School Airi: She got scolded? But she was so good...
Instructor: <Don't look down! You need to constantly focus on connecting with your audience!>
Hiyori: <Understood!>
Elementary School Airi: Sh-She's really scary...
Hiyori: <Please let me try that again!>
Elementary School Airi: You can do it, Hiyori...!
Narrator: <This is the day of her new song's release event. During the meet-and-greet portion, she has a chance to shake hands with her fans.>
Elementary School Airi: (Oh, I've been to one of her meet-and-greets before...!)
Hiyori: <You're coming to see my show? Thank you so much! I'm looking forward to seeing you there!>
Hiyori: <Wow, your ribbon's adorable! You wanted to match the costume for my new song? That's so sweet...!>
Elementary School Airi: (She has such a beautiful smile...)
Elementary School Airi: (Just seeing it is making me smile too.)
Narrator: <Following her morning session, Hiyori is able to take a break. However...>
Elementary School Airi: (Wait, she's practicing again? But she just finished doing her meet-and-greet...)
Camera Operator: <You have a pretty tough schedule. Aren't you tired?>
Hiyori: <No, I actually feel very refreshed after getting a chance to speak to my fans!>
Elementary School Airi: ...
Narrator: <Lastly, we bring you behind-the-scenes coverage of the day of her show!>
Hiyori: <I'm sorry, but can we go over the timing for the start of the song again?!>
Staff Member A: <Of course!>
Elementary School Airi: (This rehearsal feels so tense...)
Elementary School Airi: (But...)
Staff Member B: <That should be everything.>
Hiyori: <Thank you very much!>
Hiyori: <I want this show to become an amazing memory for all of you staff as well, and I'll do my best to make that happen.>
Hiyori: <So, I look forward to working with you when we do this for real!>
Elementary School Airi: (Wherever she goes, Hiyori's still Hiyori...)
Elementary School Airi: (She's always shining bright.)
Camera Operator: <What an incredible show!>
Hiyori: <Thank you! I got to see so many of my fans' smiling faces... I really had a wonderful time!>
Camera Operator: <Truly, congratulations. I feel encouraged after seeing how hard you worked for this.>
Elementary School Airi: Yeah, me too...!
Camera Operator: <So, what's your secret? How are you able to work so hard and keep on going without giving up?>
Hiyori: <Well... It's not really a secret or anything...>
Hiyori: <But I keep telling myself that it's important to have heart.>
Elementary School Airi: Huh? Heart...?
Hiyori: <My goal is to put smiles on the faces of those who are watching me.>
Hiyori: <I want them to look forward to giving the next day their very best.>
Hiyori: <I think that's why I'm able to maintain my optimism like this.>
Elementary School Airi: (Right...)
Elementary School Airi: (She really wants everyone watching her to smile and be happy...)
Elementary School Airi: (That's why Hiyori's always so dazzling.)
Elementary School Airi: I still have so much to learn... I mean, during those auditions, I was only thinking about myself.
Elementary School Airi: I'll never be able to make anyone happy if I don't—
Elementary School Airi: (Oh, but...)
Elementary School Airi: (Before...)
Lead Bully: You just kept on practicing, right? You never stopped working on your singing and dancing.
Lead Bully: After seeing that... I thought I should be doing the same thing.
Elementary School Airi: That's right...
Elementary School Airi: (I was able to help someone...)
Elementary School Airi: I guess that means I was able to take a small step forward...
Elementary School Airi: Towards my dream of becoming a dazzling idol.
